cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with video forgery detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves machine learning techniques (cs.MM) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it aims to detect and localize frame duplication in manipulated videos. The use of heuristic strategies and fine-tuning on pre-trained networks also suggests the involvement of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
